==English==
===Noun===
'''dial'''
# a [[graduated]] [[scale]] over which a [[needle]] moves to show a [[measurement]] (such as [[speed]])
# a [[clock face]]
# a [[sundial]]
# a [[panel]] on a [[radio]] etc showing [[wavelength]]s or [[channel]]s; a [[knob]] that is turned to change the [[wavelength]] etc
# a [[disk]] with [[finger]] [[hole]]s on a [[telephone]]; used to select the [[number]] to be [[called]]

===Verberb===
'''to dial'''  (''transitive'')
# to measure or indicate something with a dial
# to control or select something with a dial
# to select a number, or to call someone, on a telephone
'''to dial'''  (''intransitive'')
# to use a dial or a telephone

